<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ScrollView xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#F4F6FA"
    android:fillViewport="true">

    <LinearLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:orientation="vertical"
        android:padding="20dp">

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:background="@drawable/bg_header_card"
            android:padding="22dp"
            android:elevation="6dp">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="MIFARE Classic Study"
                android:textColor="#FFFFFF"
                android:textSize="26sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Memory layout, APDU basics, and low-level NFC flow"
                android:textColor="#DDE7FF"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:layout_marginTop="6dp" />

        </LinearLayout>

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:background="@drawable/bg_card"
            android:padding="18dp"
            android:elevation="3dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="18dp">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="MIFARE CLASSIC MEMORY STRUCTURE"
                android:textColor="#6B7280"
                android:textSize="12sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="MIFARE Classic 1K:
• Total storage: 1024 bytes
• 16 sectors
• 4 blocks per sector
• 16 bytes per block

Formula:
16 sectors × 4 blocks × 16 bytes = 1024 bytes

Sector 0:
Block 0 = Manufacturer data / UID
Block 1 = Data
Block 2 = Data
Block 3 = Sector trailer

Sector 1–15:
Block 0 = Data
Block 1 = Data
Block 2 = Data
Block 3 = Sector trailer"
                android:textColor="#1F2937"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:lineSpacingExtra="5dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

        </LinearLayout>

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:background="@drawable/bg_card"
            android:padding="18dp"
            android:elevation="3dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="14dp">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="SECTOR TRAILER"
                android:textColor="#6B7280"
                android:textSize="12sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Each sector trailer is the last block of a sector.

Structure:
[ Key A - 6 bytes ] [ Access Bits - 4 bytes ] [ Key B - 6 bytes ]

Purpose:
• Key A: Used for authentication
• Access Bits: Control read/write permissions
• Key B: Optional second authentication key

Important:
Changing access bits incorrectly can permanently lock your card sector."
                android:textColor="#1F2937"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:lineSpacingExtra="5dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

        </LinearLayout>

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:background="@drawable/bg_card"
            android:padding="18dp"
            android:elevation="3dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="14dp">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="APDU COMMAND STRUCTURE"
                android:textColor="#6B7280"
                android:textSize="12sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="CLA | INS | P1 | P2 | Lc | Data | Le"
                android:textColor="#111827"
                android:textSize="16sp"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="
CLA   Command class              00 = normal ISO command
INS   Instruction / operation    A4 = SELECT
P1    Parameter 1                Option for command
P2    Parameter 2                Option for command
Lc    Length of command data     07 = 7 bytes follow
Data  Actual command payload     AID, file ID, data
Le    Expected response length   Bytes expected back

Example:
00 A4 04 00 07 A0 00 00 02 47 10 01 00

Meaning:
CLA  = 00
INS  = A4 SELECT
P1   = 04 select by AID
P2   = 00
Lc   = 07
Data = A0000002471001
Le   = 00

Success response:
90 00"
                android:textColor="#1F2937"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:lineSpacingExtra="5dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

        </LinearLayout>

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:background="@drawable/bg_card"
            android:padding="18dp"
            android:elevation="3dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="14dp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="24dp">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="LOW-LEVEL READ / WRITE FLOW"
                android:textColor="#6B7280"
                android:textSize="12sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Step-by-step:
1. Select sector
2. Authenticate using Key A or Key B
3. Read / Write block

Commands:
AUTH A:
0x60

AUTH B:
0x61

Read block:
0x30 + block_number

Write block:
0xA0 + block_number + 16 bytes

Safe note:
Use these concepts only on your own lab cards or blank study tags.
Do not attack, clone, or modify access/payment/transit cards."
                android:textColor="#1F2937"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:lineSpacingExtra="5dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

        </LinearLayout>

    </LinearLayout>

</ScrollView>